Usage: LaunchInstance.sh [OPTIONS]

Used for launching fresh instances with or without fusion+searchhub on AWS
   -c | --cluster-size		Set the ammount of servers you would like to run fusion on, 
				will assume 1 if option is not used
   -d | --datasource-quantity	Setsthe number of datasources to index once fusion is installed
   -f | --install-fusion
				Install fusion on newly created instance(s)
   -g | --security-group-name [NAME]
				Set security group name that will be created on aws
   -i | --identity [NAME]
				Set the identity file name that will be created on aws
   -l | --fusion-license	Set the license.properties path for the fusion license
   -r | --region-name [REGION ID]
				Set the region you're server will be launched in, check online for region ID's
   -t | --twigkit-credentials	Set the path for settings.xml. Used for twigkit install
   -u | --username [USERNAME]
				Set the username that will be used for SSH and SCP protocalls,
				as well as Fusion/SearchHub home directories
   -v | --volume-size		Set ec2 volume size (32G by default)

If no options are given names will be randomly generated and given to security-group-name, and identity-name.
 

Examples:	./LaunchInstance.sh -f
		./LaunchInstance.sh -i foo -g bar -f
		./LaunchInstance.sh -l ~/foo/bar/license.properties -t ~/bear/baz/settings.xml -f
